Dataset Tips¶

  • total_bill(numerical variable) : Total bill for the table
  • tip(Numeric): Tip for the waiter serving the table
  • sex (Categorical): Gender of the bill payer (Male/Female)
  • smoker(Categorical): Whether the bill payer was a smoker (Yes/No)
  • day(Categorical): Day of the week (Sun, Mon… etc)
  • table_size(Numerical) : Capacity of the table
  • date: date and time of the bill payment

plt.title("Histogram of Passengers", size = 15)
plt.xlabel("Bin of Passengers", size = 15)
plt.ylabel("Frequency of each bins", size = 15)
density , bins, _ = plt.hist(flights["passengers"], bins = 15, alpha=0.5, color = "g")
for x,y in zip(bins, density):

        plt.text(x, y+0.05, y, fontsize=15) # x,y,str

In [23]:
figure(figsize=(20, 5))
plt.title("Count Plot of Passengers by Bins", size = 15)
ax = sns.countplot(x="binned", data=flights, alpha=0.5)
ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=40, ha="right")
plt.xlabel("Bin of Passengers", size = 15)
plt.ylabel("Count of each bins", size = 15)

for p in ax.patches:
    percentage = '{:.1f}%'.format(100 * p.get_height()/len(flights))
    x = p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2
    y = p.get_height()
    ax.annotate(percentage, (x, y),ha='center')

plt.show()

density , bins, _ = plt.hist(flights["passengers"], bins = 15, alpha=0.5, color = "g")
count, _ = np.histogram(flights["passengers"], bins)
for x,y,num in zip(bins, density, count):
    if num != 0:
        plt.text(x, y+0.05, num, fontsize=15) # x,y,str

import pandas as pd

# Setup the subplot2grid Layout
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 12))
ax1 = plt.subplot2grid((3,5), (0,0), colspan = 3, rowspan = 2) 
ax2 = plt.subplot2grid((3,5), (0,3), colspan = 2, rowspan = 2)
ax3 = plt.subplot2grid((3,5), (2,0), colspan = 2)
ax4 = plt.subplot2grid((3,5), (2,2), colspan = 3)

# Time Series
sns.lineplot(data=flights, x="year", y="passengers", hue="month", ax = ax1)
sns.scatterplot(data=flights, x="year", y="passengers", hue="month",legend=False, ax = ax1)
ax1.set_title("Time Series")

# Scatterplot
sns.heatmap(flights_wide, annot=True, fmt="d", ax = ax2)
ax2.set_title("Heatmap")

# BarPlot
sns.barplot(x='year',y='passengers',data=flights, ax = ax3)
ax3.set_title("Barplot")

# Correlation
sns.scatterplot(data=flights, x="year", y="month", size="passengers", legend=False, sizes=(20, 2000), ax = ax4)

fig.tight_layout()

group_by_iris = iris.groupby('species').mean()
group_by_iris[''] = group_by_iris[group_by_iris.columns[0]] #duplicating the first column

angle = np.linspace(start=0, stop=2 * np.pi, num=len(group_by_iris.columns))

plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))
plt.subplot(polar=True)

values = group_by_iris[:1].values[0]
plt.plot(angle, values, label='Iris-setosa', color='r')
plt.fill(angle, values, 'r', alpha=0.2)

values = group_by_iris[1:2].values[0]
plt.plot(angle, values, label='Iris-versicolor', color='g')
plt.fill(angle, values, 'g', alpha=0.2)

values = group_by_iris[2:3].values[0]
plt.plot(angle, values, label='Iris-virginica', color='b')
plt.fill(angle, values, 'b', alpha=0.2)

#labels
plt.title('Iris comparison', size=15, loc='left')
labels = plt.thetagrids(np.degrees(angle), labels=group_by_iris.columns.values)
plt.legend()

plt.show()
